Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Hit and Run of Love
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.60,0:00:06.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We visited a cake buffet after Professor \NAgasa won tickets in a lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.10,0:00:12.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}While there, we met Kitami \NSaya-san and Shono Kyona-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.73,0:00:12.32,Saya,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Kitami Saya (24)\NActress
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.84,0:00:16.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}two actresses competing for \Npopularity on their blogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.20,0:00:16.20,Kyona,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Shono Kyona (25)\NActress
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.41,0:00:23.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,However, concerned that Kyona-san wasn't \Ngetting up in time for her film shoot,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.92,0:00:26.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yonehara Sakurako-san asked a \Nhotel bellboy to unlock the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.46,0:00:29.63,DCMain,SAKURAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Kyona-san, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.23,0:00:32.34,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,They're going to start filming.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.49,0:00:36.59,DCMain,SAKURAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Kyona-san! Kyona-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.02,0:00:38.27,DCMain,SAKURAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Kyona-sa—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.41,0:00:48.57,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.28,0:00:51.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Bellhop, call an ambulance and the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.32,0:00:52.09,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.09,0:00:53.51,DCMain,BELLHOP,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.08,0:00:58.25,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.25,0:01:01.88,DCMain,SAKURAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, that's her key card, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.88,0:01:02.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.14,0:01:05.27,DCMain,SAKURAKO,0000,0000,0000,,But that doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.27,0:01:07.50,DCMain,SAKURAKO,0000,0000,0000,,This hotel's doors don't lock automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.82,0:01:08.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.43,0:01:11.54,DCMain,SAKURAKO,0000,0000,0000,,How did the murderer lock this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.20,0:01:14.18,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a locked room, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.88,0:01:18.85,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this white stain?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.59,0:01:22.65,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Whipped cream?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.26,0:01:24.36,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.57,0:01:26.52,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Who could have done this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.09,0:01:29.57,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Who would do something so cruel?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.31,0:01:32.55,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.85,0:01:36.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,With the same feelings we've \Nalways held still in our hearts,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.61,0:01:38.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,we fly powerfully into our twentieth year.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.76,0:01:42.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The key to solving the locked \Nroom case is an ordinary toy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.99,0:01:46.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth with the \Nbody of a child and the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.41,0:01:48.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.98,0:03:35.99,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(396,1)}The Actress Blogger's Locked Room Case\N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.78,0:03:34.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Actress Blogger's \NLocked Room Case, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.24,0:03:41.85,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.85,0:03:44.46,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Have you figured out\Nhow she locked the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.77,0:03:46.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.99,0:03:50.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But I know how she got in and \Nwhat she used for a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.73,0:03:55.57,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? It's really her, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.57,0:03:57.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.78,0:03:58.96,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.96,0:04:01.47,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,But she seems so nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.25,0:04:05.47,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Women are different on the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.47,0:04:10.65,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,The murder victim seemed \Nmalicious, rude, and vulgar,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.65,0:04:11.77,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,but if you look at her blog,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.77,0:04:15.48,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,you'll see she had a surprisingly \Nsensitive and conscientious side, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.87,0:04:18.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? Where'd you get that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.17,0:04:22.84,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Her nail polish bottles were \Narranged in numerical order.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.84,0:04:26.62,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,They're even a brand that you have \Nto turn over to see the number.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.98,0:04:27.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.31,0:04:31.03,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute. Then that photo...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.39,0:04:38.28,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So this is the secret she discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.83,0:04:42.51,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But would she murder her over this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.01,0:04:43.96,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.26,0:04:46.14,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.19,0:04:49.82,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In English, this...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.38,0:04:57.50,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.50,0:04:59.31,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What? Already?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.31,0:05:02.78,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you just say you were full?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.23,0:05:06.48,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Professor, can't you make anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.48,0:05:10.16,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't you go home \Nand eat a proper dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.63,0:05:16.56,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,But my parents are at a meeting \Nfor the shopping center.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.56,0:05:19.17,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,They're coming home late tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.54,0:05:24.84,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,My mom gets mad when I eat too much, \Nso let's get some kind of snack.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.84,0:05:28.12,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You had all that cake earlier, \Nand you still want snacks?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.12,0:05:31.93,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Genta-kun, you're such a glutton.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.32,0:05:34.91,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like some cheesecake, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.91,0:05:39.56,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I bought the ingredients so I \Ncould try making it tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.20,0:05:41.16,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.15,0:05:45.70,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Professor, yours is for breakfast tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.70,0:05:47.32,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Breakfast...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.61,0:05:53.01,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,But won't it take time to finish?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.01,0:05:57.04,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently it takes only thirty to \Nforty minutes in a rice cooker.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.38,0:05:58.92,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What? A rice cooker?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.43,0:06:03.94,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Cooking rice isn't the only \Nthing a rice cooker can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.94,0:06:06.92,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,It can even bake delicious cakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.57,0:06:11.21,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's it. So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.60,0:06:16.57,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit locked the room without \Nusing it for its intended purpose,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.90,0:06:20.78,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,to seal away the mistakes of the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.13,0:06:26.44,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,This case certainly is full of mysteries...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.06,0:06:32.68,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The victim said she wouldn't open the door for anyone but her assistant, Sakurako-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.68,0:06:37.33,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,but the culprit entered the \Nroom and murdered the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.84,0:06:40.26,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,And despite the doors of this \Nhotel not automatically locking,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.26,0:06:44.86,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,the key card was in the bedroom, \Nwhich is far from the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.86,0:06:49.11,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We have no idea how the culprit \Nescaped after committing the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.61,0:06:56.75,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, we still haven't found the \Nrod-like weapon used to kill the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.09,0:07:01.67,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,All we know is that the victim \Nis actress Shono Kyona-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.67,0:07:05.36,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and that there will be a great \Ncommotion about this later...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.84,0:07:08.53,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Should we ask the commissioner \Nfor instructions?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.53,0:07:10.41,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.61,0:07:13.95,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.95,0:07:14.90,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.63,0:07:18.09,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Now, hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.12,0:07:22.37,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Agasa-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.31,0:07:25.67,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.66,0:07:28.65,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,C-Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.54,0:07:32.06,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where's Agasa-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.06,0:07:36.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Professor Agasa is waiting \Nfor you in room 504.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.86,0:07:37.31,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.57,0:07:41.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Directly under this one \Nin the murderer's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.37,0:07:44.68,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,D-Directly under this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.68,0:07:47.90,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That's actress Kitami Saya-san's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.08,0:07:49.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.08,0:07:52.08,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.08,0:07:57.64,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it's difficult for you to \Nunderstand, but the room was locked, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.64,0:07:59.05,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I-Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.72,0:08:04.88,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The commissioner just called to \Nsay to do as Conan-kun says...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.88,0:08:05.71,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.80,0:08:11.72,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I-I demand an explanation!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.16,0:08:15.51,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I being suspected \Nof killing Kyona-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.00,0:08:19.94,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,The key card was in the middle of her \Nroom, so it's a locked room case, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.27,0:08:26.02,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, Kyona-san said she'd \Nonly open the door for Sakurako-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.57,0:08:30.19,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't she be your prime suspect?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.19,0:08:32.44,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.81,0:08:34.45,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But Agasa-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.49,0:08:43.43,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,You'll see how she entered the room \Nif you look through the peep hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.66,0:08:45.71,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.86,0:08:48.21,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.32,0:08:51.62,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What? Agasa-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.96,0:08:56.76,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What? Th-That's... impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.68,0:09:05.69,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What on earth...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.73,0:09:16.36,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What on earth is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.49,0:09:18.80,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.80,0:09:19.38,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.38,0:09:21.79,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,You got tricked!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.79,0:09:23.50,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It was a huge success!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.80,0:09:26.57,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,W-Was that you kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.57,0:09:28.05,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.38,0:09:32.84,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,We recorded a video of \Nthe professor on a phone
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.31,0:09:36.93,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,and played it back in front of the peep hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.40,0:09:42.43,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Then when I saw the professor \Nearlier, was that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.43,0:09:43.60,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.88,0:09:47.23,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,I had Conan-kun do the same thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.88,0:09:52.83,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Just like Saya-san did when \Nshe entered Kyona-san's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.86,0:09:55.25,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.25,0:09:59.60,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Saya-san recorded a video of \NSakurako-san with her phone
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.60,0:10:03.62,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and used it to enter Kyona-san's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.87,0:10:08.65,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,B-But I just met Sakurako-san today!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.65,0:10:11.38,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have time to \Nrecord a video like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.38,0:10:12.61,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.61,0:10:13.63,DCMain,SAKURAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.07,0:10:18.13,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Sakurako-san, when Saya-san \Nasked you to come to her room,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.43,0:10:21.28,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,wasn't something stuck to her door?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.16,0:10:24.01,DCMain,SAKURAKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Yes, an envelope...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.32,0:10:26.18,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,An envelope?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.74,0:10:27.59,DCMain,SAKURAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.59,0:10:30.69,DCMain,SAKURAKO,0000,0000,0000,,There was an envelope with a \Nlarge black heart drawn on it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.06,0:10:35.69,DCMain,SAKURAKO,0000,0000,0000,,stuck to Saya-san's door \Njust below the peep hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.13,0:10:40.20,DCMain,SAKURAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Saya-san said it was from a fan...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.48,0:10:44.20,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,There was a phone inside the envelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.58,0:10:47.76,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,By opening a heart-shaped hole in the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.76,0:10:54.71,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,lining up the phone's camera with \Nthe hole, and setting it to record,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.03,0:11:00.47,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,she was able to take a video of \NSakurako-san ringing the doorbell.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.86,0:11:06.27,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Both Kyona-san and Saya-san's rooms \Nare at the end of the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.55,0:11:09.81,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,The background in the video would \Nlook just like her hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.81,0:11:10.89,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.34,0:11:13.28,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,What about the key card?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.28,0:11:16.44,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,It was next to the body in the bedroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.79,0:11:19.58,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,This hotel's rooms don't automatically lock,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.58,0:11:23.91,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,so how did the culprit lock \Nthe door after leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.64,0:11:31.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,By using this toy helicopter you \Nwere flying around the cake buffet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.70,0:11:33.92,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,A-A helicopter?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.27,0:11:38.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could I borrow this room's key card?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.12,0:11:39.42,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.45,0:11:45.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,First, you tape a long string to \Nthe rotor shaft of the propeller
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.66,0:11:50.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and the end of the helicopter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.35,0:11:56.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,After wrapping tape around the end of \Nthe string attached to the rotor shaft,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.70,0:12:00.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,stick the tape on the key card.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.20,0:12:08.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Once you gently tape the helicopter to \Nthe bedroom floor, you're ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.01,0:12:15.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,All you have to do is pass the \Ntwo strings under the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.51,0:12:22.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,slide the key card into the slot of the \Nlocked door, and turn on the helicopter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.97,0:12:26.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The rest is up to you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.00,0:12:26.85,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.37,0:12:34.60,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,It's in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.92,0:12:36.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Start it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.80,0:12:38.04,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.04,0:12:39.36,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.55,0:12:40.86,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Ignition, on!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.45,0:12:46.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When you turn on the helicopter,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.27,0:12:53.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the string is wound around the rotor shaft, \Nand the key card slides under the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.52,0:12:57.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Once all the string has been wound up,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.81,0:13:04.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the force detaches the key card from \Nthe string and falls to the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.12,0:13:13.11,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I-I see. Instead of flying the helicopter, \Nshe used it to wind up the string.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.11,0:13:14.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.02,0:13:18.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,To finish the trick, you just pull the string\Nattached to the back from outside the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.91,0:13:21.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Pull, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.13,0:13:23.13,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.04,0:13:33.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The helicopter will be pulled off \Nthe floor and towards the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.74,0:13:39.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you pull really hard \Nonce it reaches the door...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.73,0:13:40.34,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.70,0:13:45.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,See? Now you can retrieve the string.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.75,0:13:48.37,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.70,0:13:55.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,As proof, remember the white cream \Non the floor next to the key card?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.08,0:13:57.06,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.06,0:14:02.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's because there was cream on the \Nskids on the bottom of the helicopter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.13,0:14:08.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Saya-san's helicopter crashed into \Nthe cake Genta was about to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.80,0:14:16.47,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But, Conan-kun, the helicopter's \Nstill in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.47,0:14:23.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. That's why Saya-san dropped her hat \Nthe moment she entered Kyona-san's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.01,0:14:23.71,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.27,0:14:28.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She pretended to miss the hat rack.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.26,0:14:31.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And if she stuck double-sided \Ntape on the inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.81,0:14:35.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,it should stay even if \Nshe put it on the rack.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.83,0:14:40.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So it's probably still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.92,0:14:48.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Inside her hat is the Petite Falcon \Nshe used to commit her crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.73,0:14:51.96,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,There's even string wrapped around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.96,0:14:53.92,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He must be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.92,0:14:55.17,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.56,0:14:57.05,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.05,0:15:02.59,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I-I stuck the double-sided tape \Non there so my hat wouldn't slip.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.97,0:15:08.88,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right. It must've gotten stuck \Nthere by coincidence when I dropped it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.96,0:15:13.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did you stand on the table?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.56,0:15:14.40,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.42,0:15:24.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,When my Petite Falcon got caught in the AC \Nvent, you stood on the table to get it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.85,0:15:32.69,DCItalic,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.69,0:15:35.03,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This is easier than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.52,0:15:40.04,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, oh. It's stuck in the AC.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.55,0:15:43.29,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is there some kind of stick?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.10,0:15:50.89,DCItalic,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.89,0:15:52.05,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.55,0:15:59.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There were cups on the table, so \Nnormally a person wouldn't stand on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.13,0:16:01.31,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I-I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.11,0:16:03.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And right in front of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.63,0:16:07.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,there was even a selfie stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.14,0:16:10.50,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,A selfie stick?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.29,0:16:18.69,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You can attach your phone to the end of a \Nselfie stick to take pictures of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.69,0:16:25.29,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a kind of tool. You can extend it to \Ntake pictures of yourself from far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.86,0:16:32.22,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,And it doubles as a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.90,0:16:41.28,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Most of the pictures on Kyona-san's blog are \Nselfies, but Saya-san's has none at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.90,0:16:45.73,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,So that's most likely \NKyona-san's selfie stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.96,0:16:51.13,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us, Kitami Saya-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.24,0:16:58.49,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,What is Kyona-san's selfie stick \Ndoing in your room covered in blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.78,0:17:09.13,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.29,0:17:12.37,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,She discovered my secret,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.37,0:17:18.05,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,so I used that stick to make sure \Nshe'd never open her mouth again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.44,0:17:20.05,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Your secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.39,0:17:25.76,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Look. She uploaded my secret to her blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.09,0:17:31.36,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,While pretending to introduce \Nher favorite comics.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.85,0:17:34.21,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.21,0:17:36.68,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,It's right next to her face!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.68,0:17:38.82,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,"The Hit and Run of Love!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.52,0:17:46.50,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,In Japanese, "hit and run" \Nis a baseball term, but abroad...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.53,0:17:49.77,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,It means to hit someone with your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.77,0:17:51.52,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.52,0:17:58.33,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Two years ago, I ran over \Nsome drunk man with my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.85,0:18:05.86,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd been hiding it, but when I forced \Nmy way into her room, she told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.66,0:18:14.03,DCItalic,KYONA,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with you? Has it been an hour—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.28,0:18:16.51,DCItalic,KYONA,0000,0000,0000,,S-Saya-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.51,0:18:18.11,DCItalic,KYONA,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Sakurako-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.11,0:18:19.41,DCItalic,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,She's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.78,0:18:22.03,DCItalic,KYON,0000,0000,0000,,Saya-san, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.40,0:18:24.04,DCItalic,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.04,0:18:27.79,DCItalic,KYONA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait. Stop shouting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.79,0:18:29.83,DCItalic,KYONA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.10,0:18:35.36,DCItalic,KYONA,0000,0000,0000,,Did you figure it out the code \Nin that photo of the comics?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.62,0:18:39.84,DCItalic,KYONA,0000,0000,0000,,Well? What are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.84,0:18:47.49,DCItalic,KYONA,0000,0000,0000,,Will you surrender our contest, or \Nwill you let your secret be exposed?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.51,0:18:55.73,DCItalic,KYONA,0000,0000,0000,,You might actually look \Ngood with a shaved head.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.18,0:18:59.24,DCItalic,KYONA,0000,0000,0000,,You might get a sudden influx of nun roles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.53,0:19:02.64,DCItalic,KYONA,0000,0000,0000,,It might make you even more popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.64,0:19:05.24,DCItalic,KYONA,0000,0000,0000,,And you'd have me to thank \Nfor it, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.57,0:19:07.25,DCItalic,KYONA,0000,0000,0000,,You should be grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.52,0:19:38.94,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Saya-san, I'm not sure Kyona-san \Nknew about the hit and run...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.54,0:19:40.32,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.71,0:19:42.67,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,B-But the photo...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.32,0:19:46.07,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,She said there was a code in the comics...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.07,0:19:50.97,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,The code wasn't "The \NHit and Run of Love,"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.97,0:19:54.82,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,but the series next to it \Ncalled "Looking to You."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.82,0:19:59.17,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,She's usually precise, but that series \Nalone was arranged out of order,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.72,0:20:02.07,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,and there were two copies of volume 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.02,0:20:08.99,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,If you match the volumes to the 50 \Ncharacters of the Japanese alphabet,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.99,0:20:12.25,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,read volume 29 as it is, and read \Nfrom the left, it forms a sentence...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.69,0:20:15.94,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,"Saya is 29 years old."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.39,0:20:23.45,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,That's the only code she created.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.88,0:20:27.44,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,That you'd taken five years off your age.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.85,0:20:29.45,DCMain,SAYA,0000,0000,0000,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.77,0:20:36.96,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,But blinded by bias, all you could\Nsee were the words "hit and run."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.29,0:20:41.96,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,In baseball terms, a hit \Nand run is a risky play.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.52,0:20:47.49,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,It seems your risk didn't pay off.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.72,0:22:31.28,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Agasa-san, that was another impressive \Ndisplay of detective work.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.53,0:22:32.85,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.85,0:22:34.29,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.60,0:22:38.71,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Conan-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.42,0:22:42.96,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I was surprised to learn \Nyou know the commissioner.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.22,0:22:48.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? But isn't the commissioner \Nof Section One Matsumoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.02,0:22:49.17,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.17,0:22:55.77,DCMain,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you'd help solve the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.27,0:23:06.48,DCMain,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,The Sleeping Kogoro's bag of wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.38,0:23:11.99,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.33,0:23:22.00,DCMain,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Kuroda Hyoe. I've taken over as \Ncommissioner of Section One of the MPD.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.47,0:23:24.50,DCMain,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,It's nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.82,0:23:27.90,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.23,0:23:30.51,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,It's nice to meet you as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.73,0:23:39.52,DCMain,KURODA,0000,0000,0000,,And it's nice to see you \Nagain, Edogawa Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.74,0:23:53.86,DCMain,BOY,0000,0000,0000,,There's no such things as aliens.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.11,0:23:56.99,DCMain,BOY,0000,0000,0000,,They do exist! My dead dad said so!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.99,0:23:58.74,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's an alien! Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.19,0:24:06.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There might be something \Nbehind last night's incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.37,0:24:08.96,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it's our time to shine.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Disappointing and Kind Alien
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.74,0:24:13.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is \N"The Disappointing and Kind Alien!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.99,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Cold Medicine
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.80,0:24:32.89,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.89,0:24:34.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Cold medicine!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:36.38,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}A person who takes cold medicine...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:39.98,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.38,0:24:37.36,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}...but just watches...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.36,0:24:38.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.23,0:24:39.22,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}They're watching out for a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.22,0:24:39.88,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yeah, yeah.
